The paper deals with power-constrained sensing matrix design in a sparse Gaussian linear dimensionality reduction framework, which involves optimization techniques and performance evaluation criteria commonly used in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper considers noisy channels, which is a common problem in communication systems (cs.SI).
